    {
      "text": "All of the following are cold sterilization methods except?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "UV rays"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Autoclave"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Gamma rays"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Plasma sterilisation"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Autoclave is heat <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f39be0f0871692777199459d86e0a7\">sterilization</span> of 121•*15min*15psi.</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"NA\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"NA\" data-source=\"NA\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"4167\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/jNSkD5Ani0HDEPZfq97u1741790733.png\" width=\"2970\" /></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>An <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b4786b5c79169277718298b7590c38\">autoclave</span> is a sterilisation technique that uses moist heat at a temperature > 100<sup>o</sup>C.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b4786b5c79169277718298b7590c38\">autoclave</span> (steam steriliser) works on the principle of steam production under pressure.</li>\n\t<li>When this steam meets a cooler surface, it condenses, transferring its heat to that surface. The process continues until the surface temperature matches that of the steam.</li>\n\t<li>The resulting condensed water provides moist heat, effectively killing microbes on the materials by protein denaturation.</li>\n\t<li>Its temperature settings are 121<sup>o</sup>C for 15 minutes at 15 <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"536157be41169277719622efea0d20\">psi</span> pressure.</li>\n\t<li>Materials that can be sterilised include linen, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> instruments(non-sharps only), laboratory ware, pharmaceuticals, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"90dcd6e02316927771990a5c253ff7\">suture</span> material except catgut(cold sterilisation) and culture media except egg and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1ffaec13de169277719828374cfda0\">serum</span> containing media(inspissation).</li>\n\t<li>Sterilisation control indicator - <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a1f8bd55901692777188b383607b48\">Geobacillus</span> stearothermophilus</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Types of Autoclaves in Healthcare:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Laboratory autoclaves</li>\n\t<li>Hospital <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5d07a26d7516927771863e5f43d8d0\">dressing</span> sterilisers</li>\n\t<li>Instrument sterilisers</li>\n\t<li>Rapid <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"579dcf5fc51692777185eef17a83c6\">cooling</span> sterilisers</li>\n</ul>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [
        "https://image.prepladder.com/content/jNSkD5Ani0HDEPZfq97u1741790733.png"
      ],
