    {
      "text": "Which test is used in the detection of long term glucose tolerance?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Fasting blood glucose"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Random blood glucose"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "HbA1C"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "CBC"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: C) HbA1C</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>HbA1C</strong> (Glycated hemoglobin) is the test used to assess long-term <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"af3ae60c0c16927771889b84ca41c0\">glucose</span> tolerance and the average <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"88b48cf7241692777183e5f5b8adf1\">blood sugar</span> levels over the past 3 months. It reflects the percentage of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ad2073fe6716927771885f3c1ec652\">hemoglobin</span> that has <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"af3ae60c0c16927771889b84ca41c0\">glucose</span> attached to it, providing an indicator of overall <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"88b48cf7241692777183e5f5b8adf1\">blood sugar</span> control.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Fasting blood <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"af3ae60c0c16927771889b84ca41c0\">glucose</span> (Option A)</strong>: This measures <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"88b48cf7241692777183e5f5b8adf1\">blood sugar</span> levels after <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"67f123756d16927772026c46b8d27e\">fasting</span> for at least 8 hours. It is useful for diagnosing diabetes but does not provide a long-term view of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"af3ae60c0c16927771889b84ca41c0\">glucose</span> tolerance.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Random blood <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"af3ae60c0c16927771889b84ca41c0\">glucose</span> (Option B)</strong>: This measures blood <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"af3ae60c0c16927771889b84ca41c0\">glucose</span> at any time of the day, regardless of when the person last ate. It is useful for diagnosing diabetes, but again, it does not provide a long-term assessment.</p>\n\n<p><strong>CBC (Complete Blood Count) (Option D)</strong>: This is a blood test that measures various components of the blood, such as red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets. It is not related to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"af3ae60c0c16927771889b84ca41c0\">glucose</span> metabolism.</p>",
