    {
      "text": "Stain used to demonstrate fungal elements are?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Acid fast stain"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Gabbet's stain"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Methenamine silver"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Leifson & Ryu's stain"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: C) <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cb3712727816927771925665b0b1e0\">Methenamine</span> silver</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Methenamine silver stain</strong> is commonly used to <strong>demonstrate fungal elements</strong> in tissue samples. This <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b29a1a16ab1692777199ede1c6e28b\">stain</span> binds to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"97294d26a21692777184b7ddc59c4e\">cell wall</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5ab0081e8316927772037e0f7c5a79\">fungi</span> and highlights the fungal structures, allowing them to be clearly visualized under the microscope. It is particularly useful in detecting fungal infections in tissues, as it stains the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5ab0081e8316927772037e0f7c5a79\">fungi</span> in a <strong>black</strong> color against a <strong>light background</strong>, making identification easier.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Detection Methods for Fungi:</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Method</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Description</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Use</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Direct Microscopic Examination</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>KOH Preparation</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Dissolves <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d0e68b82ed1692777190fa10f7d4ba\">keratin</span> in clinical specimens (e.g., skin scrapings, nail clippings) to visualise fungal elements.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Diagnosing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"84b9a43a7816927771867efa42a2dd\">dermatophyte</span> infections</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Calcofluor White Staining</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Enhances fungal visibility by binding to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b24b4918a916927771844114519396\">chitin</span> in cell walls, causing them to fluoresce under UV light.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Observing fungal morphology</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Gram Stain</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Traditionally for bacterial identification; also useful for yeasts, which typically <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b29a1a16ab1692777199ede1c6e28b\">stain</span> Gram-positive (purple).</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Detecting certain fungi</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>India Ink Preparation</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Negative <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3b007026bd16927771997ae809b603\">staining</span> method for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e26ba9a1d41692777187d0ad03a8c1\">encapsulated</span> yeasts (e.g., Cryptococcus neoformans), revealing a clear <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"95af91681416927771887742113c38\">halo</span> around cells.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Identifying <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e26ba9a1d41692777187d0ad03a8c1\">encapsulated</span> yeasts</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Methenamine Silver and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1e835060d3169277719499350aabe5\">PAS</span> Staining</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Histochemical techniques that <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b29a1a16ab1692777199ede1c6e28b\">stain</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5ab0081e8316927772037e0f7c5a79\">fungi</span> black (methenamine) or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9038419f6f169277719188195b72b5\">magenta</span> (PAS) in tissue sections.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Highlighting <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5ab0081e8316927772037e0f7c5a79\">fungi</span> in tissues</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Lactophenol Cotton Blue (LCB) Mount</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Enhances contrast in teased fungal colonies for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55beab619216927771925caac38373\">morphological</span> observation.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Microscopic examination of fungi</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Serology</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Antibody Detection</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Identifies antibodies produced by the host in response to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5ab0081e8316927772037e0f7c5a79\">fungi</span> using methods like ELISA.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Tracking <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"dc6add5cf91692777189b30a6bae38\">immune response</span> to fungal infections</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Antigen Detection</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Detects fungal antigens in body fluids using techniques such as <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"60088572d31692777191346a90b73f\">latex</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"36e1a07ab01692777180db73f01e84\">agglutination</span> tests.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Identifying fungal presence in the body</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Skin Tests</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Delayed-Type Hypersensitivity (DTH)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Assesses previous exposure to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5ab0081e8316927772037e0f7c5a79\">fungi</span> through localised reactions to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6a367ebd0c169277719091155a5b0f\">injected</span> antigens.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Evaluating past fungal exposure</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Newer Rapid Diagnostic Tests</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Nucleic Acid Hybridisation</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Uses labelled DNA probes for rapid fungal DNA <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"723fdec66b1692777186e92f0c6fdf\">detection</span> in clinical samples.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Quick identification of fungal pathogens</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Polymerase Chain Reaction (PCR)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Amplifies specific fungal DNA sequences, enabling early diagnosis even with low fungal loads.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Early <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"723fdec66b1692777186e92f0c6fdf\">detection</span> of fungal infections</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Acid fast <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b29a1a16ab1692777199ede1c6e28b\">stain</span> (Option A)</strong>: This is used primarily for <strong>Mycobacterium species</strong> (e.g., <strong>Mycobacterium tuberculosis</strong>), not fungi. The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"440f2b916316927771808b8ad44a64\">acid-fast</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b29a1a16ab1692777199ede1c6e28b\">stain</span> highlights <strong>acid-fast bacilli</strong> by coloring them red, but it is not useful for fungal elements.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Gabbet's <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b29a1a16ab1692777199ede1c6e28b\">stain</span> (Option B)</strong>: This is not a commonly used <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b29a1a16ab1692777199ede1c6e28b\">stain</span> for fungi. It is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0efdcdc9e01692777201003c81c85a\">variant</span> of Gram staining, primarily used for bacterial identification, not for fungi.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Leifson & Ryu's <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b29a1a16ab1692777199ede1c6e28b\">stain</span> (Option D)</strong>: This is a <strong>staining method for bacteria</strong>, especially to highlight <strong>flagella</strong> in bacterial samples, and it is not used to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b29a1a16ab1692777199ede1c6e28b\">stain</span> fungal elements.</p>\n\n<p> </p>",
